{"name": "ml-feature-toolkit", "metadata": {"name": "ml-feature-toolkit", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/HishamSalem/pymltools", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy", "pandas", "scikit-learn", "xgboost", "shap", "optbinning", "SALib", "scipy", "statsmodels", "tqdm", "matplotlib", "seaborn", "joblib"], "summary": "A package for analyzing feature interactions in machine learning models", "upload_time": 1735767093}, "documentation": ["# pymltools\n\nA comprehensive Python toolkit for analyzing feature interactions in machine learning models, combining multiple methodologies to provide deep insights into feature relationships and their impact on model behavior.\n\n## Features\n\n### Interaction Analysis Methods\n- **SHAP Interaction Analysis**: Leverages SHAP values to detect and quantify feature interactions\n- **Feature Binning Analysis**: Uses optimal binning techniques to identify non-linear relationships\n- **Sensitivity Analysis**: Implements Sobol indices to measure feature interaction effects\n\n### Key Capabilities\n- Statistical significance testing for interactions\n- Visualization of interaction effects\n- Multiple testing correction\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install ml-feature-toolkit\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pymltools.feature_binning", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pymltools.feature_binning.FeatureBinningAnalyzer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pymltools.feature_binning.FeatureBinningAnalyzer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pymltools.feature_binning.FeatureBinningAnalyzer.get_feature_iv", "asynchronous": f